results.name: Number of distinct terminal subtrees of the rooted tree with Matula-Goebel number n.
link: Index entries for sequences related to Matula-Göbel numbers
example: 20 is the Matula-Goebel number of the tree (oo((o))), which has 4 distinct terminal subtrees: {(oo((o))), ((o)), (o), o}. So a(20) = 4.
